"The moon, shining." Often used in reference to single-edged curved blades in various transliterations, such as [[Pedang Candrasa]]. In Malay the transliteration is //cendera//.

[ext[https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/cendera#Malay]]:

<<<
!!Etymology
From Sanskrit `चन्द्र` (//candra//, “moon”), from `श्चन्द्र` (//ścandrá//, “shining, radiant”).
<<<

