<<<
!!Etymology 1

From Sanskrit `चन्द्र` (//candra//, “moon”). Compare Malay [[cendera|?]].

!!!Noun
//candra//

# (literary) moon (natural satellite) Synonyms: bulan, rembulan, kamar
# (literary) moon (personified as a deity)

!!Etymology 2
From Sanskrit `चन्द्र` (//candra//, “glittering, shining (as gold), having the brilliancy or hue of light”).

!!!Particle

# used in the form mencandrakan (“to depict; to illustrate”)
# used in the form pencandraan (“depiction; illustration”)

!!Alternative forms
cendera
